The Meta Genesis Engine (MGE)

The Meta Evolution Engine evolves.

The Meta Genesis Engine creates new spaces in which evolution can occur.

Evolution assumes:

* an environment,
* variation,
* selection.

Genesis asks:

Can we invent a better environment?

Instead of evolving fish into birds…

…it invents the sky.

⸻

Four Powers

1. World Generation

Don’t optimize inside the game.

Generate new games.

Different constraints.

Different physics.

Different objectives.

⸻

2. Objective Generation

Most optimizers accept a goal.

Genesis asks:

Was that the right goal?

It searches over objective functions themselves.

⸻

3. Primitive Discovery

Don’t invent new tools.

Invent new atoms.

Examples historically:

* number
* zero
* function
* algorithm
* information
* feedback

Each wasn’t just another concept—it became a new primitive from which many other concepts could be built.

⸻

4. Dimension Creation

This is probably the highest leverage.

Don’t move better through an existing space.

Ask whether the space itself is missing a dimension.

Longitude wasn’t an optimization.

It changed navigation.

Probability wasn’t merely another number.

It changed reasoning.

Information theory wasn’t another branch of math.

It changed communication.

The biggest leaps often come from discovering a coordinate that wasn’t previously represented.

