The Love / Logic Question

I actually wouldn’t put one above the other.

I’d think of them as complementary optimization pressures.

* Logic asks: Is this internally coherent?
* Love asks: Does this help living beings flourish?

Without logic, care can become ineffective.

Without care, logic can optimize toward outcomes people would reject.

So rather than “love then logic” or “logic then love,” I’d model them as two orthogonal axes that constrain each other.

           High Logic
                ↑
                │
      Wise      │     Precise
                │
────────────────┼────────────→ High Care
                │
     Aimless    │     Compassionate
                │

The upper-right quadrant—high coherence and high care—is where you’d want many human-centered systems to aim.

